President Obama announced his intent to nominate Eric Goosby as Ambassador at Large and Global AIDS Coordinator at the Department of State, and Paul N. Stockton as Assistant Secretary of Defense (Homeland Defense and Americas' Security Affairs) at the Department of Defense. Goosby, currently the CEO and Chief Medical Officer of Pangaea Global AIDS Foundation, has extensive experience in HIV/AIDS treatment and prevention strategies. Stockton, a senior research scholar at Stanford University, specializes in U.S. security institutions' response to threats and the restructuring of national security budgets and policies. President Obama expressed confidence in their abilities to tackle challenges and ensure the safety of the American people.